  "description": "Details of condition 3 (detailed drawings of a hard and soft landscaping scheme) required by planning permission 22/AP/118 for the  Construction of a single storey ground floor side-infill extension with three rooflights, a window and door to the side and sliding doors to the rear; the installation of an additional window to the side of the existing property; and alterations to the front garden to facilitate an off-street car parking space, including new hard and soft landscaping and the removal of a section of the existing front boundary fence. 22/AP/1185Alterations to the front garden hard and soft landscaping to accommodate for the new parking bay. Existing T1 is to be removed along with the central asphalt path. The parking area will be surfaced in new golden gravel with a perimeter edge to meet the public pavement in a single row of red brick pavers to minimise gravel spillage. The remainder of the garden (leftover where asphalt path is removed) is to be infilled with new top soil to form a continuous planter bed, and replanted with existing leftover spring flowers. T3, SHB 06 and SHB 07 are to replanted within the continuous planter bed.\r\rPlease refer to documents 105_A1000 Existing, 105_A2000 Proposed Drawings, 105_73 Burbage Road Landscaping Schedule",
